rComments: He's a kind and caring prof. Very knowledgeable and makes an attempt to learn everyone's name (in a class of 50+, that's an impressive feat). The course was very interesting and I learned a lot about Latin America--course topics are also very diverse, which means a little bit for everyone. However, lectures can get a bit boring and monotone.
The lecture is quite dry and he does indeed use many examples from his own work to illustrate concepts. However, the group work is valuable and he is helpful during the process.
most useless course ever. prof is way over enthusiastic, the class is more like a verbal biography of his past jobs in  amazon and mexico that no one is interested in.
A nice man who is genuinely interested in other students' opinions. But, there's too much of an emphasis on readings and doesn't hand back assignments until end of term.

This professor was awesome! He makes an extra effort to get to know his students, which I have never had before!  Attendance isn't mandatory, but if he knows you, and sees you in class, then your mark will most likely be MUCH higher than those that don't attend.  Just saying...

Professor Abizaid was an awesome professor! He actually took the time to learn the names of everyone in our class, which I have never seen before. Very entertaining and passionate about his work, and very easy to talk to. Some of the projects can be a pain, but they are alot more unique and easy than anything from any other class. Highly recommend!
